observations.recommendation:
8.14. We recommended that the Municipal Mayor, as Chairman of the MDRRM Council, and the MDRRM Officer ensure full implementation of PPAs identified in the LDRRMFIP in order to effectively increase the level of preparedness of the municipality during natural calamities;
8.15. We also recommended that the Municipal Budget Officer, MDRRM Officer and the Municipal Accountant ensure that the LDRRMF are appropriated and spent solely for disaster-related activities as contemplated in the NDRRMC, DBM and DILG’s JMC No. 2013-1.
8.16. During the exit conference, the concerned LGU personnel explained that the noted disbursement for encoding of barangay DRRM plans was necessary since the preparation/encoding of said plan is very technical as it involves comprehensive plans. Nonetheless, they agreed to comply with the audit recommendations.

12.10 We recommended that the designated GAD Focal Person:

     1. Coordinate and assist the different divisions/units of the  LGU  in
        identifying activities which are GAD responsive;
     2. Integrate or consolidate the inputs from other Departments  in  the
        LGU’s Annual GAD Plan and Budget;
     3. Prepare the Annual GAD Plan and Budget and submit the same  to  the
        reviewing agencies within the period prescribed by regulations;
     4. Prepare GAD Accomplishment  Report  based  on  the  inputs  of  the
        departments/units;
     5. Provide the Audit Team with copies of the GAD Plan and  Budget  and
        Accomplishment Report once these  are  approved  by  the  reviewing
        agency.
